## The Bank's Receivables Turnover Ratio

The  Bank's  receivables  turnover  ratio  was  improving,  as shown by the decline in gross NPL and Net NPL ratios in 2023,  compared  to  those  of  2022.  Gross  NPL  ratios  in 2023  and  2022  were  1.48%  and  1.99%,  respectively. Whereas, net NPL ratios in 2023 and 2022 were 0.95% and 1.33%, respectively.

In reducing non-performing loans, the Bank has taken the following measures:

- 1. Issue Notification Letter on late payment to the Bank;
- 2. Issue Warning Letters I, II, and final;
- 3. Issue a summon to make a formal appearance to the Bank;
- 4. Perform collection by visiting non-performing debtors;
- 5. Conduct deliberation to debtor who will sell collateral asset or other assets outside the collateral;
- 6. In  the  event that the non-performing debtor still has business prospects to be revived, a restructuring will be proposed;
- 7. If the above measures do not settle the non-performing loans, collateral will be taken over and then be recorded as foreclosed collateral; and
- 8. If the debtor cannot cooperate, a legal process will be carried out.

