- 3. Disclosure of remuneration determination procedures for the Board of Directors and Board of Commissioners based  on  GMS  resolutions,  whose  authority  can  be delegated to the Board of Commissioners;
- 4. Capability, responsibility, performance achievement of each member of the Board of Commissioners;
- 5. Capability and  performance  achievement  of  each member of the Board of Directors with key indicators, such as Bank profits, sales growth, risk portfolio, and productivity;
- 6. Performance  indicators to measure  the Board of Directors'  performance,  such  as  achievement/growth of  financial  targets  (profits,  assets,  CASA,  and  NPL); success in increasing/maintaining the Bank's soundness level; as well as the realization and Bank Business Plan that have been set;
- 7. Level of technical expertise, workload, experience, and educational background;
- 8. Capability in overcoming the risks and problems faced by the Bank;
- 9. Fairness with due observant of the peer groups; and
- 10. Other related factors that are not contradictory to laws and regulations.

