- 6. Evaluating whether the Company's liquidity level can be achieved optimally at an acceptable cost level;
- 7. Recommending annual financial planning in the form of  basic  assumptions  of  Bank  Indonesia  economic indicator figures and banking financial ratios in general (peer's banks);
- 8. Evaluating the projected liquidity gap analysis calculation; and
- 9. Evaluating stress test results from the Risk Management on  Assets  and  Liabilities  due  to  chang-es  in  interest rates and foreign exchange rates on the market, in the event the stress test re-sults could potentially harm the Bank's liquidity.

